.TH RANDOM 3 "2025" "Nightingale" "Nightingale Library Functions"
.SH NAME
random, srandom \- random number generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <stdlib.h>
.PP
.B long int random(void);
.BI "void srandom(unsigned int " seed ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR random ()
function uses a non-linear additive feedback random number generator
to return successive pseudo-random numbers.
The
.BR random ()
function returns a value between 0 and
.BR RAND_MAX .
.PP
The
.BR srandom ()
function sets its argument as the seed for a new sequence of pseudo-random
integers to be returned by
.BR random ().
These sequences are repeatable by calling
.BR srandom ()
with the same seed value.
.PP
If no seed value is provided, the
.BR random ()
function is automatically seeded with a value of 0x1478123.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR random ()
function returns a value between 0 and
.BR RAND_MAX .
.PP
The
.BR srandom ()
function returns no value.
.SH NOTES
The Nightingale implementation uses a simple custom PRNG algorithm.
This is not cryptographically secure and should not be used for
security-sensitive applications.
.PP
The quality of randomness is suitable for simulations, games, and
non-security testing purposes.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rand (3),
.BR srand (3)
